<task id="R7-005" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>Implement Validate() — Action FK required; Tool + Document NOT required (FR-13)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <wave>1</wave>
    <estimated-effort>1-2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>bff-api, code-impl, wave-1</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>002</dependencies>
    <fr-coverage>FR-13 (validation contract)</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Replace the task-002 Validate() skeleton with the binding contract from FR-13: Action FK is REQUIRED
    (AiCompletion is prompt-driven and cannot run without a prompt source); Tool FK is PROHIBITED;
    Document FK is PROHIBITED. Return NodeValidationResult with explicit per-error messages so the
    orchestrator can fast-fail before any LLM cost is incurred. Tests in task 009 assert the contract.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET backend developer. The contract here is binding semantics — get the message text right so
    consumers (Playbook Builder UI, orchestrator logs, error responses) can show users exactly which field
    is wrong.
  </role>

  <goal>
    AiCompletionNodeExecutor.Validate() complete:
    1. Returns NodeValidationResult.Failure if context.Action is null OR context.Node.ActionId is missing
       — error message: "AiCompletion node requires an Action FK (prompt source). Set sprk_actionid on the node."
    2. Returns NodeValidationResult.Failure if context.Tool is present
       — error message: "AiCompletion node MUST NOT have a Tool. Tools are used by AiAnalysis nodes; AiCompletion is prompt-only."
    3. Returns NodeValidationResult.Failure if context.Document is present
       — error message: "AiCompletion node MUST NOT have a Document. Documents are used by AiAnalysis nodes for grounding; AiCompletion is prompt-only."
    4. Returns NodeValidationResult.Failure if context.Node.OutputVariable is null or whitespace
       — error message: "AiCompletion node requires OutputVariable to be set on the node."
    5. Returns NodeValidationResult.Failure if Action.SystemPrompt is null or whitespace
       — error message: "AiCompletion node's Action {ActionId} has no SystemPrompt. Set sprk_systemprompt on the Action."
    6. Aggregates all errors into a single NodeValidationResult.Failure result (don't bail on first error)
    7. Returns NodeValidationResult.Success only when ALL conditions pass
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="scaffolded-executor">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiCompletionNodeExecutor.cs</file>
    <file purpose="pattern-decision">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/aicompletion-pattern-decision.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="sibling-validation">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/EntityNameValidatorNodeExecutor.cs</file>
    <file purpose="reference-llm-validation">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiAnalysisNodeExecutor.cs</file>
    <file purpose="interface">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/INodeExecutor.cs</file>
    <file purpose="bff-constraints">.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-13">Validation: requires Action FK; does NOT require Tool; does NOT require Document. Fast-fail via NodeValidationResult.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-06">Action FK is OPTIONAL at SCHEMA level but required at executor Validate() for prompt-driven executors (AiAnalysis, AiCompletion, AiEmbedding). This is the AiCompletion enforcement point.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI Minimalism — Validate() does not require any new dependencies beyond what the task-002 ctor already injects (logger only).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">BFF AI Architecture — Validate() is a leaf-executor concern; do not introduce a new validation framework.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Testing Strategy — task 009 covers each error path. Validation logic must be deterministic + side-effect-free (no logging at warning+ level for ordinary validation failures; rely on caller to log).</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10">BFF Hygiene — placement unchanged.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md §F">Test update obligation — task 009 covers Validate() error paths.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>ai/node-executor-authoring</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ai/node-executor-authoring.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-013-bff-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-038-testing-strategy.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="EntityNameValidatorNodeExecutor.Validate" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/EntityNameValidatorNodeExecutor.cs">
        Sibling Validate() pattern. Aggregates errors into a List&lt;string&gt;, returns NodeValidationResult.Failure with all messages, else NodeValidationResult.Success. AiCompletion follows the same shape with different conditions.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="NodeValidationResult.Failure / Success" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/">
        Existing result type. Accepts string[] error messages. AiCompletion uses it identically.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task 002 scaffolded Validate() with a TODO. This task fills in the contract from FR-13. The key
      semantic distinction: AiCompletion is prompt-only — it requires the Action (for SystemPrompt + OutputSchema
      + Temperature) but prohibits Tool + Document (which are AiAnalysis-only concepts for grounded calls).
      The Playbook Builder UI (Wave 8) consumes these messages directly in the form's error display.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="002" status="not-started-but-required">AiCompletionNodeExecutor.cs scaffolded with Validate() skeleton.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
